{{Infobox ethnic group | group = Malaysians of Timorese origin | image = | population = Hundreds<ref name="Gunn2010">{{cite book|author=Geoffrey C. Gunn|title=Historical Dictionary of East Timor|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=c7zHoj5fZ6wC&pg=PA71|date=18 December 2010|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-7518-0|pages=71–}}</ref> | popplace = [[Sabah]] | langs = [[Malay language|Malay]], [[Indonesian language|Indonesian]], [[Tetum language|Tetum]] and [[East Timorese Portuguese|Portuguese]] | rels = [[Roman Catholicism]], [[Protestant]], [[Islam]] | related = [[Demographics of East Timor]], other [[ethnic groups in Indonesia]] }}
The '''Timorese Malaysians''' or '''Florenese Malaysians''' consists of people of full or partial [[Timor]]ese descent who were born in or immigrated to [[Malaysia]]. Timorese in Malaysia consist mainly of Timorese resident from the Indonesian [[West Timor]] as well as recent migrants from [[East Timor]]. Most of the Timor has come since the [[Indonesian occupation of East Timor|occupation of East Timor]] by [[Indonesia]]. Most of these Timorese are mainly reside in the state of [[Sabah]] especially on the east coast area of [[Tawau Division]] with some of them had [[Interracial marriage|intermarried]] with the local peoples.<ref name="Gunn2010"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pascal.iseg.utl.pt/~cesa/History_of_Timor.pdf|title=History of Timor|work=Lisbon School of Economics and Management|publisher=[[University of Lisbon]]|accessdate=15 August 2015|page=6}}</ref>
== Relations between the state of Sabah and East Timor == Since the independence of East Timor from Indonesia, the first President of East Timor [[Xanana Gusmão]] has paid a visit to the state of Sabah on a working visit and to see the Timorese communities there.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.nst.com.my/top-news/timor-leste-pm-arrives-in-sabah-1.544634|title=Timor-Leste PM arrives in Sabah|work=[[Bernama]]|publisher=[[New Straits Times]]|date=2 April 2014|accessdate=15 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/news-asia/2014/04/03/sabah-university-timor-leste-ink-mou-oil-and-gas-industrial-training|title=Sabah university, Timor-Leste ink MoU on oil and gas industrial training cooperation|work=Bernama|publisher=[[The Brunei Times]]|date=3 April 2014|accessdate=15 August 2015}}</ref>
